+/* Combined peer filter for both peer-table admission and DISCO probing.
+ * Layers the optional "priority only" mode on top of the httpd allowlist: when
+ * disco_priority_only is set (single-peer deployments that only talk to the
+ * priority peer), every peer other than the priority peer is filtered out so we
+ * stop holding/probing the rest of the tailnet — cutting both per-peer RAM and the
+ * DISCO/handshake control traffic that otherwise steals throughput from the data
